    "comment": "Rationale: The paper demonstrates that autophagy is required for LTD at Schaffer collateral synapses. Fig. 7 shows that both conditional knockout and shRNA knockdown of ATG5 disrupts the maintenance of LTD induced by either low-frequency stimulation, or the application of NMDA, or of the group 1 mGluR agonist DHPG. ATG5-cKO also leads to altered cognitive flexibility (Fig. 8).. Experimental description: \"The mice were maintained in a pathogen-free environment and housed in groups of five animals per cage with constant temperature and humidity and a 12 h/12 h light/dark cycle.\" (p.17)",
